# Presentation Layer

Views render UI and forward user actions to the Notifier. No business logic, no repository access, no GoRouter calls.

## Widget type

- **`ConsumerWidget`** (or `ConsumerStatefulWidget`) for views observing Riverpod.
- **`StatelessWidget`** for extracted sub-widgets with no local state.
- **`StatefulWidget`** only when local UI state is required (animation, scroll controller).
- **No `flutter_hooks`** on this project — Riverpod covers app state; use `StatefulWidget` for rare local UI needs.

## Extraction rules

- Extract sub-widgets as named classes (`BoardGrid`, `CellTile`), never as `_buildXxx()` methods.
- One public widget per file; file name = class name in snake_case.
- Prefer `const` constructors and `const` widget instances wherever possible.
- Maximum widget tree depth: **4 levels** — extract before nesting further.

## View responsibilities

```dart
class GameView extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final state = ref.watch(gameNotifierProvider);
    return BoardGrid(
      onCellTap: (cell) => ref.read(gameNotifierProvider.notifier).playMove(cell),
    );
  }
}

```

The View reads state via `ref.watch`, invokes Notifier commands via `ref.read(...).notifier`.

## Async and lifecycle

After any `await` before using `BuildContext`, check **`context.mounted`**:

```dart
await ref.read(gameNotifierProvider.notifier).playMove(cell);
if (!context.mounted) return;
ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar(...);
```

Use `mounted` inside `State` classes. Never trigger navigation from `build()`.

## Theming

No hardcoded colors or text styles. Use `AppThemeContextX` — `context.colors`, `context.typos`, etc. See `design-system.mdc`.

## Game end screen (TIC-6)

No dedicated route. The end state is derived from `GameStatus` (`won`, `draw`) — single source of truth.

Show a `GameEndOverlay` widget inside `GameView` when `state.status != GameStatus.playing`:

```dart
if (state.status != GameStatus.playing)
  GameEndOverlay(
    status: state.status,
    onPlayAgain: () => ref.read(gameNotifierProvider.notifier).playAgain(),
    onGoHome: () => ref.read(gameNotifierProvider.notifier).goHome(),
  ),

```

- **Rejouer** → Notifier calls `StartGameUseCase` (stays on `/game`)
- **Retour accueil** → Notifier calls `HomeNavigation.goHome()` via navigation abstraction

Do not navigate to `/game/end` on game over. Do not trigger navigation from `build()` when status changes.

## Forbidden

```dart
// ❌ business rule in widget
if (board.cells.every((c) => c != null)) { ... }

// ❌ navigation in view
context.go('/home');

// ❌ build helper returning widget
Widget _buildBoard() => GridView(...);
```
